      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Star mare CAPTAINS MISTRESS NZ (8) stretched her record at this circuit and distance to five from six when she cruised home over the best of the mares for a dominant Queen Elizabeth II Mile win last start. Kept up to the mark with a trial win since and while she tackles a strong field of males this time she has the speed to go forward from this draw so can deliver again. HI MANAMEISJEFF NZ (10) kept his manners in check and returned to winning form last week, his third success from his last four attempts. Has put together a terrific strike rate at the Menangle mile and has proven before that he can win from wide barriers. PINSEEKER NZ (9) draws wider than last week but there was merit in that performance when only 1.5m behind Hi Manameisjeff after working. NYACK (11) is first up for eight weeks and draws wide but has trialled and did beat a handy field at this circuit and distance when last seen. SEASIDER (1) continues to perform well. The inside draw can see him competitive again.",
